The U.K. Export Credit GuaranteeDepartment (ECGD) said it would change the system of premiumsit levies from British exporters, reducing their costs whenthey tender for a contract abroad.    It said in a statement that the changes involved halvingthe rate of non-refundable premiums levied by the ECGD fromexporters before the contract they tender for is allocated. Therates of additional premium paid by successful tenderers willrise. The last overhaul in premiums was in 1984 when charges forcover rose sharply after several years of heavy losses. REUTER&#3;